<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7449> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7449" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Tr. pl. 56. His RE number should probably be (2), since the L. Racilius in Cic. Verr. (2.2.31) could be the father of the tribune. He in turn was probably one of the conspirators against Q. Cassius Longinus in Spain in 48 (Bell. Alex. 52-55). (TJC) See Wiseman, NM 255, no. 354; Shackleton Bailey, Studies 63.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5141> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5141" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Supported the optimate stand against Clodius and the Triumvirate (Cic. QF 2.1.2, and 4.5; Fam. 1.7.2; Planc. 77; Schol. Bob. 165f. Stangl)." .
